## Symlink map

The `skills/` directory contains symlinks that resolve to skill directories outside the workspace.

| Link path (in repo) | Symlink target | Target contents | How to restore target |
|--------------------|---------------|-----------------|----------------------|
| `skills/[SKILL_NAME]` | `[TARGET_PATH]` | [SKILL_DESCRIPTION] | `git clone [CLONE_URL] [TARGET_PATH]` |

---

## Setup steps

Run these commands in order on a new machine to reproduce the full working environment.

```bash
# 1. Create required base directory structure
mkdir -p [BASE_DIR]/skills
mkdir -p [BASE_DIR]/workspaces

# 2. Clone skill dependencies (symlink targets must exist before cloning the workspace)
# [SKILL_NAME]
git clone [CLONE_URL] [TARGET_PATH]

# 3. Clone the workspace to the exact required path
git clone [WORKSPACE_REMOTE_URL] [ABSOLUTE_WORKSPACE_PATH]

# 4. Validate symlinks resolve correctly
ls -la [ABSOLUTE_WORKSPACE_PATH]/skills/
# Should show symlinks — no "No such file or directory" errors
```

---

## Validation checklist

Run these checks after setup to confirm the environment is working:

- [ ] All external dependency paths exist and are non-empty
- [ ] All symlinks in `skills/` resolve without errors (`ls -la skills/`)
- [ ] Each symlink target contains the expected skill files
- [ ] Claude Code can open the workspace: `cd [ABSOLUTE_WORKSPACE_PATH] && claude`
